ala, a river, [184](vp061.htm#page_184).\n\nCholas, a people, [193](vp061.htm#page_193).\n\nChronology, system of; [22](vp037.htm#page_22), of the kings of the Kali age,\n[484](vp117.htm#page_484).\n\nChulaka or Chuluka, a river, [182](vp061.htm#page_182).\n\nChunchu, a prince, [373](vp095.htm#page_373).\n\nChyavana, a sage, [354](vp093.htm#page_354). s. of Mitrayu,\n[454](vp112.htm#page_454). s. of Suhotra, [455](vp112.htm#page_455).\n\nCleanliness, rules of, [300](vp085.htm#page_300).\n\nClepsydra, water clock, described, [631](vp158.htm#page_631).\n\nClouds, how formed, [230](vp067.htm#page_230). classes of,\n[231](vp067.htm#page_231), n. [3](vp067.htm#fn_711). the shell of the\nuniverse, ib.\n\nColebrooke, notices of the Vedas, [i](vp001.htm#page_i). of the Puran\xcc\x81as,\n[v](vp001.htm#page_v). of the Saraswata Brahmans and language,\n[lxvii](vp028.htm#page_lxvii).\n\nColonization of India, [lxv](vp028.htm#page_lxv).\n\nCosmogony of the Hindus, [10](vp036.htm#page_10). analogies with ancient,\n[13](vp036.htm#page_13), note [18](vp036.htm#fn_131).\n\nCreation, accounts of; [11](vp036.htm#page_11). [34](vp039.htm#page_34).\n[39](vp039.htm#page_39). (primary), mode of, [13](vp036.htm#page_13). course\nof; [14](vp036.htm#page_14). various kinds of, [36](vp039.htm#page_36).\n(secondary), periods of, [27](vp038.htm#page_27). kinds of,\n[35](vp039.htm#page_35). of mankind, [36](vp039.htm#page_36). of properties,\n[37](vp039.htm#page_37). a property of Brahma, [21](vp037.htm#page_21).\nfunction of Vishn\xcc\x81u as Brahma, [19](vp036.htm#page_19), &c.\n\n* * *\n\n[Next: D](vp167.htm)\n\n'